        <updateDate>2020-01-09T17:17:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>End the Limo Loophole Act </b></p> <p>This bill revises the definition of commercial motor vehicle to include vehicles that are designed to transport 9 or more passengers including the driver (currently, at least 16 passengers including the driver) and requires the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration to finalize a rulemaking to require states to implement an annual inspection program for commercial passenger-carrying vehicles.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
